  <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
  {faq.map((f) => (<details><summary>{f.q}</summary><p>{f.a}</p></details>))}

  <h2>Bottom line</h2>
  <p>SQL and NoSQL aren't rivals so much as tools for different shapes of data. <strong>SQL</strong> wins on structure, consistency and rich querying - the default for relational, correctness-critical data. <strong>NoSQL</strong> wins on flexibility and horizontal scale - the default for schema-less data and internet-scale writes. Pick based on your data and access patterns, and don't be afraid to use both.</p>
